ENTRY            30508   20260324   20260508   20260508       3222
SUBENT        30508001   20260324   20260508   20260508       3222
BIB                 10         39
TITLE      Fission yields in the symmetric region yields of the
            stable isotopes of tin and cadmium in the thermal
            neutron fission of 235U and 239Pu
AUTHOR     (C.K.Mathews)
INSTITUTE  (3INDTRM,1CANMCM)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,15,344,1977)
EXP-YEAR   (1973)
FACILITY   (REAC,1CANMCM)
SAMPLE     The samples of 235U (enriched to 93%) and 239Pu were
            purified by anion exchange with hydrochloric acid. The
            purified solution was evaporated into quartz
            irradiation vials, flamed to convert to oxide form,
            and sealed in vacuum. Each vial contained 10 mg 235U
            or 8 mg 239Pu respectively.
METHOD     (CHSEP) The fission product tin and cadmium were
            separated from the irradiated samples by an anion
            exchange method that had been standardized before.
            Contamination from naturally occurring isotopes was
            minimized by performing the extraction procedures in a
            dry box set up in a fume hood with a high rate of
            exhaust.
           (ASEP) The isotopic analysis was carried out on a 38 cm
            radius tandem mass spectrometer, which was operated at
            a resolution = 1000. A modified electron impact ion
            source (described by De Laeter and Thode in Can. J.
            Phys. 47(1969)1409) was used. Its sensitivity to tin
            was enhanced by adding to the tin-sample (about 25
            nano-g) 1 microliter of 0.7sm phosphoric acid. Since
            this procedure produced a molecular ion peak at mass
            124, some tin separations were done without phosphoric
            acid, in order to also measure 124Sn.
CORRECTION The mass discrimination was determined by analysis of
            natural tin samples. The resulting correction of
            1.5 percent/mass unit was also used to correct the
            Cd - abundances.
HISTORY    (19790907C) TL.
           (19800729U) ML. Reaction changed from ratio to relative
           (20040311U) SD: corrected 4-dig. year and lower cases.
           (20260324A) VT. Entry revised
ENDBIB              39
COMMON               1          3
EN-DUMMY
