SUBENT        30508006   20260324   20260508   20260508       3222
BIB                  7         18
REACTION   (92-U-235(N,F)MASS,CHN,FY,,MXW)
METHOD     The relative Cd-yield data were normalized to mass=111.
            The yield of mass=113 was established by smooth
            extrapolation of the curve through masses 111 and 112.
            Then the yield of mass=114 was obtained by subtraction
            of the 113-yield from the normalized measured sum of
            relative abundances of masses 113+114.
            The tin-yields were matched to normalized Cd-yields
            by placing the 117Sn yield on a smooth curve towards
            the normalized 116Cd yield.
FLAG       (1.) Yield of 76 year 122mSn
MONITOR    (92-U-235(N,F)47-AG-111,CUM,FY,,MXW)
MONIT-REF  (,W.H.Walker,R,AECL-3037/2,1973)
STATUS     (TABLE,,C.K.Mathews+,J,PR/C,15,344,1977) Table III
           (DEP,30508002)
           (DEP,30508003)
HISTORY    (20260324A) VT. Data restored for fixed value and
            STATUS updated
ENDBIB              18
